1.10	La_rabbia	La rabbia	La Rabbia ("Rage") is an Italian documentary film produced by Gastone Ferranti and directed by Pier Paolo Pasolini in the first half and by Giovannino Guareschi in the second half. The two directors comment newsreels reporting then current events such as the Hungarian Revolution of 1956, the Cuban Revolution, Marylin Monroe's death and the Italian economic miracle and each gives a reply as to what causes the rage and anguish which seem to dominate the world.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0c/La_rabbia.jpg/220px-La_rabbia.jpg
